11501 James Watt Drive - Actual Site Plan
11501 James Watt Drive - Conceptual Site Plan

Common.SpaceDescription.Common.Text: The surrounding area is comprised of a mixture of retail / commercial and industrial properties.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
11501 James Watt Drive is situated within the Vista del Sol submarket, adjacent to both the El Paso International Airport and Fort Bliss. The Property is therefore convenient to a wide range of local amenities which include the Las Palmas Shopping Center, Alamo Drafthouse and a multitude of restaurants. Downtown El Paso is just 20 minutes away, offering a vibrant place to live, shop and visit. Nearby hotels include Holiday Inn Express, Marriott’s Towne Place Suites and Hampton Inn and Suites, which serve as important business services amenities for the Property.

The property is located in East El Paso near the Zaragoza / George Dieter / Interstate 10 interchange, providing employees with ease of access and proximity to the continually expanding “Eastside” residential. The vast majority of El Paso’s labor pool reside within a 5 mile radius of the Loop 375 corridor in East El Paso.
